KANO – Muhammad Al Amin Little, a veteran governorship aspirant weekend bought the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Intent Form to run in the familiar turf come 2023 general election. Al Amin Little, a soccer star who cut his teeth on youth football in Kano and environs in the late ’70s lost the 2003 APP ticket to Malam Ibrahim Shekarau, contested on the platform of PRP the same year and lost. Little who until lately had cult-like followership among the youth in the state had been in out of PDP, and APC between 2011 to date. The enfant terrible of Kano politics narrowly lost becoming Deputy Governor to Umar Ganduje following the resignation of his earthswile Deputy, and Professor of Nutrition, Professor Hafiz Abubakar in 2019. An attempt by the Kano politician to stage a comeback in 2019 was truncated by bandits who shot him in his farm along Birnin Gwari General area in 2019. The devastating attack forced Little to went on the break only to recoup and stormed the turf on Friday with a photo show of his appearance at PDP headquarters in Abuja where he picked the intent form. At the moment PDP, Kano Chapter is in the hands of Kwankwaso, a two-term governor of the state who served out a term at the Red chamber in 2019.